definitions.definition: The lowest (and usually the largest) square sail hung on the foremast
A square fore-and-aft sail set on the foremast, but behind it, on a schooner or other similar vessel.
A triangular sail set forward of the foremast : forestaysail .

main_definition: ( nautical , on a square-rigged ship ) The lowest (and usually the largest) square sail hung on the foremast
secondary_definitions: ( nautical ) A square fore-and-aft sail set on the foremast, but behind it, on a schooner or other similar vessel.
( nautical , on a sloop ) A triangular sail set forward of the foremast : forestaysail .
